news.title: Residents protest in Sancoale against proposed Bhutani Infra development project
news.para: Gathering under the banner of Sancoale Against Mega Project (SAMP), the protesters demanded that state govt revoke any construction licence issued to the multi-dwelling housing project with immediate effect.

news.title: MCD proposes Rs 1,144 crore plan to replace four lakh LED lights across four zones
news.para: The proposal, costing Rs 1,144.3 crore, also includes the operation and maintenance of lights for 10 years. It will be presented in the House meeting on Monday for administrative approval and expenditure sanction.

news.title: Bengaluru civic body to survey under-construction buildings
news.para: The move follows the collapse of an under-construction building at Babusapalya near Hennur last week in which nine people were killed.

news.title: Kerala: Vilappilsala mini-township project likely to be scrapped
news.para: The works related to the Rs 400 crore project, planned at the old waste treatment plant, came to a standstill earlier this year. Although earlier, the corporation officials expressed hope that the project could be revived, the chances are slim.

news.title: NCLT dismisses JC Flowers’ Rs 70 crore claim against HDIL
news.para: NCLT said, "ruling that the debt did not qualify as a “financial debt” under the Insolvency and Bankruptcy Code (IBC) as it was not due or payable at the time of HDIL’s corporate insolvency resolution process (CIRP) commencement."

news.title: Over 8,000 flats registered in Greater Noida under rehabilitation policy
news.para: Another 8,000 flats are likely to be registered by March next year, according to a report presented to the Greater Noida Industrial Development Authority's (GNIDA) board on Sunday.

news.title: Noida authority approves two more projects under co-development policy
news.para: Noida authority has approved two projects under Uttar Pradesh’s co-development policy, allowing Nimbus Projects and Theme County to revive stalled projects in sectors 168 and 115, respectively. The initiative aims to aid 1,000 homebuyers and ensures payment of dues and financial closure by the new developers.

news.title: Jaipur development body set to expand by 1,000 sq km, with 272 more villages
news.para: "A meeting chaired by JDA commissioner Anandhi will be held in early Nov to finalise the proposed area extensions under the JDA's jurisdiction in the Master Plan 2047," a JDA official said.

news.title: Land acquisition set to begin for New Noida
news.para: Conceptualised as DNGIR (Dadri Noida Ghaziabad Investment Region), New Noida will be built across around 20 villages of GB Nagar and 60 of Bulandshahr, which will make it identical in size to Noida city.

news.title: Bengaluru civic body to remove EC requirement to apply for e-khata
news.para: ​This decision is set to streamline the process by removing the need for property owners to obtain an EC, which often involves delays and fees of up to Rs 5,000, particularly for properties registered before 2004.

news.title: Bengaluru: Meeting NGT norms essential for apartments to get Cauvery water supply
news.para: ​​After 17 years of waiting, these areas now have access to drinking water from the Cauvery. The BWSSB is ready to provide water to the 55,000 connections already established and plans to extend new connections to applicants within 15 to 30 days.

news.title: New law soon to curb illegal construction in Bengaluru: Karnataka CM
news.para: Siddaramaiah said Bruhat Bengaluru Mahanagara Palike (BBMP), Bengaluru Development Authority (BDA), and Bengaluru Metropolitan Region Development Authority (BMRDA) will be empowered to crack down on illegal constructions.

news.title: Gurugram: Drains overflow, FIR against developer for releasing wastewater
news.para: This led to overflowing of drains in various areas including Dhanwapur, Surat Nagar phase 1 and 2, Rajendra Park, Vishnu Garden, and Ratna Garden.

news.title: Mangaluru: Nagarashraya Samiti to select beneficiaries for PMAY in Idya
news.para: The Nagarashraya Samiti has decided to prepare a new list of beneficiaries by cancelling the names of those who did not pay instalments, failed to submit documents, and others who did not show interest in availing the houses.

news.title: Satellite villages in Vijayawada in dire need of basic infrastructure
news.para: Despite being located on the banks of the Krishna River, many villages lack safe drinking water facilities, as the groundwater in these areas has been found unsafe for consumption due to higher levels of silica and fluorine.

news.title: About 77 flats registered in two societies of Greater Noida
news.para: Since March, the department issued 930 flat registries to buyers while 270 remain pending since Saturday's camp.There are about 1,200 flats in Migsun Ultimo Society. The project started in 2014.

news.title: Tamil Nadu CM, union minister review Chennai metro rail phase-II project
news.para: Stalin said that work is progressing quickly for the phase 2 (118.9 km, 3 corridors) project and so far Rs 19,229 crore has been spent. He thanked PM Modi and the Centre for accepting his request and approving phase 2 as central sector project.

news.title: Agra to be developed as 'solar city'
news.para: In fact, the state govt has prepared a plan to develop all the districts of the Agra division as solar cities. Accordingly, streetlights and govt offices will be solar-powered.
